@startuml
title Blind Plan Execution (Context Isolation)

actor User
participant LLM

User -> LLM : Task: "Solve complex problem X"

LLM -> User : Plan:\n1. Do A\n2. Do B\n3. Do C

note right of User
User extracts plan
and removes it from
context
end note

====

User -> LLM : [Context: Task only]\nExecute step 1: Do A

note right of LLM
LLM doesn't see:
- Full plan
- Final answer
- Other steps
end note

LLM -> User : Result of step 1

====

User -> LLM : [Context: Task + Result1]\nExecute step 2: Do B

LLM -> User : Result of step 2

====

User -> LLM : [Context: Task + Result1 + Result2]\nExecute step 3: Do C

LLM -> User : Final answer: Y

note right of User
Benefit: LLM cannot
"fit" reasoning to 
pre-decided answer
(honest reasoning)
end note

@enduml
